ssf: mathoaw mara'in a shanaotoan Choa-Ing-Bon pato'iaw goan-co-min a patashan
english: President Tsai Ing-wen's Apology to the Indigenous Peoples on Behalf of the Government.

ssf: maposhaz qamishan a thoini, mita wa hian- hoat polhipathan a patashan, san-paw pingqthan mzai goan-co-min. haya sa sonda goan-co-min a lhanaz, mataliza to itia shmararozi a lhanaz shororoniza, po'apaw izai goan-co-min mzai naor Taiwan a talima wa thao. miazitho milhilhi, thoini amoqthawan kmangqtha tata wa kinangqtha. yako amia'awan cing-ho masai goan-co-min-cok pato'iaw. monsai mashpatiz shaba wa qamishan, pashtay manoin goan-co-min-cok inangqto manion kashpar masa anto manazitho, yako mia'awan cing-ho pato'iaw manion goan-co-min- cok.
english: On this day 22 years ago, the term "shanbao" (mountain people) in the Additional Articles of our Constitution was replaced with the proper name: "indigenous people." This correction not only did away with a discriminatory term, but also highlighted the status of indigenous peoples as Taiwan's "original owners." From this basis, today, we are taking another step forward. To all indigenous peoples of Taiwan: On behalf of the government, I express to you our deepest apology. For the four centuries of pain and mistreatment you have endured, I apologize to you on behalf of the government.

ssf: yako mriqaz, kahiwan konathathoinian inai mingqolhmoz itiawan mani sa thao mzai ingqaiza pato'iaw. izai sa yako amia'awan cing-ho pato'iza a lalawa. rinataqan ita anto manazitho zain thaythoy naor amiazitho, rinataqan ita wa nomanoma, naor mita thao a shinkodaan naor ita thao amiazitho a shkoda, haya inai yako thoini milhilhi, mangqto yako mzai apingqthan mindamriz minshoqish.
english: I know that even now, there are some around us who see no need to apologize. But that is the most important reason why I am representing the government to issue this apology today. To see what was unfair in the past as a matter of course, or to treat the pain of other ethnic peoples as an unavoidable part of human development, this is the first mindset that we, standing here today, resolve to change and overturn.

ssf: thoini apasik malalabaza wa lalawa malhinona manion, mino qa amatsai goan-co-min-cok pato'iaw. inai Taiwan a proq mashpatiz shaba wa qamishan naoriza sa thao inai, inai a thao naor mrataq thaythoy ananak a ininthawan. itia thaythoy a lalawa, itia thaythoy a kazakazash, itia thaythoy a shashomshom, itia mani thaythoy a ininthawan a proq. kanoniza makitnanai itia tata qbit a thao anto minakikalhi min'ananakiza makonanai mriway inai a proq.
english: Let me put in simple terms why we are apologizing to the indigenous peoples. Four hundred years ago, there were already people living in Taiwan. These first inhabitants lived their lives and had their own languages, cultures, customs, and domains. But then, without their consent, another group of people arrived on these shores, and in the course of history, took everything from the first inhabitants who, on the land they have known most intimately, became displaced, foreign, non-mainstream, and marginalized.

ssf: sasaz a lalawa wa shompazaw mzai miarikorikos a thao matsai mimamoqtha wa thao nomanoma ingqolhmozin thitho kmalaw. naor ininai a thao minamaza oka sa proq a'ianan, nomawan inai mingkakalongkon, oka sa taon a'ianan, minmiazai sa aminakantoa wa thao, miaqay isai thaythoy a proq min'ala'alash, noma thoini miazai sa anto talima wa thao, min'ishirshiriza wa thao. tata qbit a thao a mindado, miazai sa inisai miaqbit a thao a shkoda. miazai ita anto manazitho a kok- ka, ya miazitho haya wa sasaz a lalawa iabrith ita mriqaz, izai sonda wa nomanoma polhkiz po'apaw malhinona. ya miazitho, sa mathoaw izai amonsai s acing-ho tiasasaz a lalawa sonda shnaw amingqtha mangqto, haya inai yako thoini milhilhi malhinona.
english: The success of one ethnic people can be built on the suffering of another. Unless we deny that we are a country of justice, we must face up to this history. We must tell the truth. And then, most importantly, the government must genuinely reflect on this past. This is why I stand here today.

ssf: itia tata wa patashan thitho a lhanaz mzai "Taiwan a sasaz a lalawa" thitho miahala tata wa qahil mzai, "Taiwan naor oka sa sasaz a lalawa, Horan a thao miahala monai, noma Te-sing-kong thitho sa miahala mani monai malhkakrikriw, noma ti Ching-koq mintamaz malhkakrikriw." haya sonda Shpoot a sasaz a lalawa wa mriqaz. goan-co-min- cok naoriza pizza wa matilaw a kawash to inaiza, itia manasha sa thaythoy a kazakazash, noma thaythoy a inin'ania, makitdaodaok powanaz. kanoniza moqay yamin pasai makoshwit a qbit a thao a mriqaz matash sasaz a lalawa, miazitho amiz'awan yako matsai cing-ho pato'iaw.
english: There is a book called "The General History of Taiwan" published in 1920. In its foreword are these words: "Taiwan had no history. The Dutch pioneered it, the Koxinga Kingdom built it, and the Qing Empire managed it." This is a typical Han view of history. The truth is that indigenous peoples have been here for thousands of years, with rich culture and wisdom that have been passed down through generations. But we only know to write history from the perspective of the dominant. For this, I apologize to the indigenous peoples on behalf of the government.

ssf: Horan noma Te-sing-kong a cing-ho monsai Alishay mathoaw kmaipathay noma kmalaw sa proq masa kmalaw sa ininthawan a farifariw a aniamin, noma to shiwanin izai Cing-koq lhongqizi, mathoawiza kmaipathay mapa'oroshrosh a talhom, noma to Litpooniza sa lhongqizi mathoawiza mara'iniza wa anto pidaza sa goan-co-min-cok, miazai sa kmiskis sa goan-co-min-cok. miazithoiza shaonanai Tiong- hoa-min-koq-cing-ho miazitho mani goan-co-min apinshpootan dai. Lashpaat shaba wa qamishan, mashtay monai Taiwan a cing-ho mingqolhmoz pasain thaythoy mashampanaq noma kmalaw sa goan-co-min-cok a proq, mathoaw pingqarman sa goan-co-min-cok naor itia wa nomanoma. miazitho, yako amia'awan cing-ho pato'iaw.
english: The Dutch and the Koxinga Kingdom massacred and exploited the Pingpu ethnic group. The Qing Empire presided over bloody confrontations and suppression. Colonial Japan put in place comprehensive savage policies. And the post- war ROC government undertook assimilation policies. For 400 years, every regime that has come to Taiwan has brutally violated the rights of indigenous peoples through armed invasion and land seizure. For this, I apologize to the indigenous peoples on behalf of the government.

ssf: Goan-co-min-cok pasain thaythoy a kazakazash lhongqizi naor itia wa nomanoma, noma pasain mani Goan-co-min-cok a kafazaqin a kazakazash lhongqizi hodon masa wazaqan nomanoma, miazitho mashtay maqitan lhongqizi. kanoniza thoini a kok-ka kmalawa wa rinataqan, sa Goan- co-min-cok anto manion a min'ananak kmalawa ananak a palhkakrikriw, noma mani mot'oka sa ananak lhongqizi a koshwit. noma sasaz a shidoq molawashwash, noma naor min-cok a miasoon a ininthawan anto shnoron mani sa soma. miazitho mani amonsai yako cing-ho pato'iaw.
english: Indigenous peoples maintain tribal order according to traditional customs, and ecological balance according to traditional wisdom. But in the process of modern state-building, indigenous peoples lost the right to steer their own course and govern their own affairs. The fabric of traditional societies was torn apart, and the collective rights of peoples were not recognized. For this, I apologize to the indigenous peoples on behalf of the government.

ssf: Gona-co-min-cok naoriza thaythoy itia thaythoy a lalawa, noma pasain thaythoy a kazakazash a kafazaqin lhongqizi thaythoy nomanoma wa ininthawan. kanoniza shwanin Litpoon lhongqizi, apiazain manion apinlitpoon a thao, apingqthan thitho minlitpoon, shaonatosi tata makatanatho shpaat larima wa kawash, cing-ho apin'oka sa naam a lalawa, min'oka sa gona- co-min-cok a lalawa. mashtaan sa Alishay a lalawa min'okaiza. molhkiz minakanantoa wa cing-ho, anto monsai gona-co-min-cok a kazakazash makarishkish lhongqizi, miazitho mani amonsai yako cing-ho pato'iaw.
english: Indigenous peoples had their own languages. However, with Japanese rule aiming to assimilate and turn all into imperial subjects, and with the ROC government banning tribal languages after 1945, indigenous peoples' languages suffered great losses. Most Pingpu languages have disappeared. Successive governments have been negligent in the protection of indigenous cultures. For this, I apologize to the indigenous peoples on behalf of the government.

ssf: kahiwan, cing-ho isoi Yami a thao anto kafazaqin izai ho-hoi-liaw pisain thaythoy Yami a thao a proq. pingqarman sa Yami a thao, miazitho mani amonsai yako cing-ho pato'iaw.
english: Without the knowledge of the Yami tribe, the government stored nuclear waste on Orchid Island. Tribe members on the island had to suffer the negative consequences. For this, I apologize to the Yami people on behalf of the government.

ssf: minakantoa cing-ho shaonanai Taiwan, isai tanaraos a Alishay mathoaw pikrarozin sa cing-fo, tatata wa lhongqizi a cing-ho mingqolhmoz miko ping'oka sa Alishay a goan-co-min a tinoran. miazitho amonsai yako Alishay pato'iaw.
english: Ever since outsiders began arriving in Taiwan, the Pingpu ethnic group on the western plains have born the brunt of the impact. One ruling power after another eroded the individual and collective identities of the Pingpu ethnic group. For this, I apologize to the Pingpu ethnic group on behalf of the government.

ssf: min-coo pingqthaniza, noma kok-ka itia shontaam goan-co-min-cok a pinalhinona wa nomanoma. cing-ho itia mani minalhinona noma kinalawa ladado a palhkakrikriw. thoini yamin itia maqitan a shompazaw sa "goan- co-min-cok a naor itia wa fat," kanoniza izai a fat anto sa cing-ho miazitho a mabrith. mita wa kinalawa anto mabiskaw, ani mani mingqolhmoz, ani mani maqitan kinalawa. miazitho mani amonsai yako cing-ho pato'iaw.
english: After the democratic transition, the country began to respond to the appeals of indigenous movements. The government made certain promises and efforts. Today, we have an Indigenous Peoples Basic Law that is quite advanced. However, government agencies have not given sufficient weight to this law. Our actions have not been fast enough, comprehensive enough or sound enough. For this, I apologize to the indigenous peoples on behalf of the government.

ssf: Taiwan mzai manasha sa kazakazash a proq, kanoniza shaonathathoinian, goan-co-min- cok a maqitan a makalingkin, minfazaq noma farifari, cing-ti......nomanoma wa piakazash, miazitho mani monsai anto goan-co-min-cok a thao itia mara'in a anto tataal. tataal thoini, monsai goan-co-min-cok mriqaz shmalarozi. miazitho mani oka nanashnash. cing-ho anto manasha sa kinalawa, nomawan goan-co- min-cok mathoaw shkoda, nomawan sh'oka. miazitho mani amonsai yako goan-co-min- cok pato'iaw.
english: Taiwan is known as a culturally diverse society. But even today, indicators on health, education, economic livelihood, political participation and more still show gaps between indigenous and non- indigenous peoples. Meanwhile, stereotypes and even discrimination against indigenous peoples have not gone away. The government has not done enough, so indigenous peoples have suffered pain and frustration unknown to other ethnic peoples. For this, I apologize to the indigenous peoples on behalf of the government.

ssf: ita anto shdoo iningkarishkishan, tatata wa minalangqtha molhkiz ani yamin to makarishkish. noma manion mathoaw shkoda, shaonathathoinian mani miaqawan shkoda. yako monmanion mathoaw amazaiza! thoini a pato'iaw mathoawiza shrikkosan, kanoniza thoini lhmazawan. ani yako to mzai lashpaat shaba wa qamishan goan-co-min-cok a shingkodaan noma piaqarman az'az sh'oka, kanoniza yako monsai shnaw mangqto thoini a pato'iaw, izai a kok-ka wa itmaz a thao lhmazawan mapaqaqitan.
english: Our efforts have fallen short, and succeeding generations have been blind to this inadequacy. Because of this, your hardship has continued to this day. For this we are truly sorry. Today's apology is long overdue, but it is a beginning. I do not expect any one speech or phrase of apology to wipe away four centuries of pain and suffering by the indigenous peoples. But I do hope with all my heart that today's apology will set this country and all its people on the path towards reconciliation.

ssf: malalawa manion yakin pasain tata wa goan- co-min-cok a lalawa pishfazaq manion to thoini a miasosoon. isa Taiyal a lalawa, "dado" mzai "Sbalay," izai Taiyal a lalawa isa balay a ianamoqtha poqthaan "S" minsbalay. "dado" masa "mapaqaqitan" itia sa tataal a inangqto. pariri tata wa lalawa palhinona, sonda wa mapaqaqitan amathoaw yamin mabahba mriqaz dado a palhkakrikriw. ya miazitho shdooiza mokakton.
english: Please allow me to shed light on this occasion with a piece of indigenous wisdom. In the Atayal language, truth is called "Balay," and reconciliation is called "Sbalay," so you simply add an "S" sound to "Balay." Truth and reconciliation are in fact two related concepts. In other words, only by facing the truth sincerely can reconciliation be attained.

ssf: isa goan-co-min-cok a kazakazash a itmaz, ya itia sa thao mapathay sa soma wa thao, ya mangqto amapaqaqitan, tanatoqash a thao, thitho sa malalawa pishdohalan a thao, noma pingqarmanin a thao molhkizin thitho malalawa posoon. miasoon anto mzai apato'iaw, apalhinona thaythoy mabaraz a lalawa, ya malhinona sonda wa palhkakrikriw, noma tanatoqash pashtay malhintal miqilha tata barokoz a qilha. rinataqan ita piazithoiza mrataq, haya mzai "Sbalay." mangqto yako mzai thoini mzai cing-ho masa goan-co-min-cok a Sbalay. rinataqan a moririw polhkizin po'apaw malhinona, ani yako to poil, ani
english: In indigenous cultures, when a tribe member has offended another and intends to reconcile, an elder brings together the offender and the offended - not to produce a direct apology, but to allow each side to frankly share their inner journeys. When this truth-telling concludes, the elder calls for everyone to drink together, so that what is past is truly past. This is "Sbalay."

ssf: yako to smamik. italhawan itia mani goan-co-min-cok a horoy amalhinona thitho a inangqto. ani yako to malhinona manion thoini mzai piazithoiza, kanoniza yako amalalawa manion rinataqan a moririw niza to amaqaqtha, haya wa kok-ka, itia tata wa qali mashtay amapaqaqitan.
english: I hope today's occasion can be a "Sbalay" between the government and the indigenous peoples. I have spoken of past mistakes and truths the best I can, with nothing held back. In a moment, our indigenous friends will speak. I do not dare ask you to forgive, here and now. But I sincerely ask you to sustain the hope that past wrongs will not be repeated, and that one day, this country can see true reconciliation.

ssf: thoini moqay tata wa lhmazawan, kazaiko amopaqaqitan anto isai goan-co-min-sok masa Alishay, is acing-ho. mafazaq yako, ya moqay rozith a pato'iaw, anto sonda wa pato'iaw, monsai goan-co-min-cok molhkiz a palhkakrikriw izai a kok-ka ashiroan dado amapaqaqitan.
english: Today is only a beginning. The duty for reconciliation lies not with the indigenous peoples and the Pingpu ethnic group, but with the government. I know that words of apology alone are not enough. What we actually do for the indigenous peoples will decide whether reconciliation succeeds or stumbles.

ssf: a'inai yako dado a pishfazaq, mathoaw mara'in a shanaotoan a taon amakalawa sa "goan-co-min- cok a sasaz a lalawa dado masa patongkariri wa malhkaktha," yako amonsai kok-ka mara'in a shanaotoan, minananak yako posoon a thao, yako amonsai tatata wa cok a mia'azo mashtay mosoon kmilhim sonda tiasasaz a lalawa, mashtay mani malhkaktha haya wa kok-ka kahiza wa lalawa.
english: Therefore, I am here to announce that we are setting up an Indigenous Historical Justice and Transitional Justice Commission under the Presidential Office. As the head of state, I will serve as convener and work hand in hand with tribal representatives to pursue historical justice. We will also discuss, on the basis of equality, the future policy direction of this country.

ssf: amalhinona yako, mathoaw mara'in a shanaotoan a taon a malhkaktha, sa sonda mabrith izai kok- ka masa goan-co-min-cok mashtay manazitho a inra'inan. tatata wa cok a mia'azo molhkiz masa Alishay a mia'azo, molhkiz cok masa kataonan a miasoon a riniqaz, az'az minbangqir. ya miazitho a kinalawa to goan-co-min-cok a pashtay miasoon a palhkakrikriw, shdoo goan-co-min-cok a shnaw a inangqto a lalawa po'apaw.
english: I want to stress that this commission places the greatest importance on equality between the country and the indigenous peoples. The election of tribal representatives, including for the Pingpu ethnic group, will take as basis the consensus of peoples and tribes. This commission will serve as a mechanism for collective decision-making by indigenous peoples, and will ensure that the voices of tribe members find true expression.

ssf: miaqbit, yako amathadoq hing-cing-inn amalhkaktha "goan-co-min-cok naor mita wa fat a smokos malhkaktha." haya wa palhkaktha pino'apaw a lalawa, min mita w acing-ho kmalawa palhkakrikriw a piakazash. haya wa palhkakrikriw mingqolhmoz sasaz a lalawa wa inangqto, goan-co-min-cok min'ananak lhongqizi thaythoy a palhkakrikriw, manazitho a farifariwan a palhkakrikriw, noma pinfazaq masa kazakazash a polhaqlha, noma boot a makalingkin a lhongqizi, noma isa mawalhnaq a goan-co-min-cok lhongqizi nomanoma.
english: In addition, I will request that our Executive Yuan convene regularly the Indigenous Peoples Basic Law Promotion Committee, and use the Yuan's authority to coordinate and handle matters related to any consensus reached by the above-mentioned commission. These matters include the following: to retrieve historical memories, to promote indigenous self-government, to seek fair economic development, to ensure continuation of culture and education, to safeguard indigenous health, and to protect the rights of urban indigenous peoples, etc.

ssf: thoini a fat monsai goan-co-min-cok a kazakazash itia sa anto mobalabalay, ita amakalawa s izai itia sa kazakazash tnoran a fat, zain "goan-co-min-cok a fat a malhkakrikriw a ifazfaz a taon," miazitho kmalawa apot'oka goan-co-min-cok a kazakazash masa kok-ka wa fat anto anto mobalabalay.
english: Where modern laws and indigenous traditional cultures are at odds, we will set up an Indigenous Legal Service Center with a high degree of cultural sensitivity, to reduce through institutional design the growing clashes between indigenous customs and modern laws.

ssf: yamin thoini amonsai cing-ho thmadop iahiaw kmalawa kmashiqitan, goan-co-min-cok maqa thaythoy a kazakazash isa thaythoy a proq moribosh, anto mzai afariwin thaythoy, moribosh anto lhqizin a lhkaribosh, anonin dai qa asakpin noma alomin? yamin thoini amonsai izai a lalawa qazii ya amiakoza.
english: I will ask the relevant agencies to immediately pull together cases in which indigenous community members have been indicted or sentenced for hunting, where the hunting was done in accordance with traditional customs, on traditional lands, and for non-transactional needs, and where the animals hunted were not protected by conservation laws. For such cases we will deliberate solutions.

ssf: yako amonsai cing-ho thmadoq, amafazaq mino sa ho-hoi-liaw apisain Lan-so? po'apaw izai dado a lalawa. sa ho-hoi-liaw ya niwan to kinashiqitan cing- ho apolhipas Yami a thao sa nomanoma.
english: I will also direct relevant agencies to present an investigative report on the decision-making process of nuclear waste storage on Orchid Island. Before finding a permanent solution for the nuclear waste, we will provide the Yami tribe appropriate compensation.

ssf: tataal a thoini, atondoo Alishay a monsai thaythoy a ananak a shnoro, shnoron Alishay a goan-co-min a thitho a lhanaz. yamin makatanatho a foraz noma matoroz a qali miahala, amalhkaktha fat a lalawa, amaqa ongqtoan sa Alishay a goan-co-min-cok a lhanaz, noma thaythoy a lhinqizi noma thaythoy a shoqromin.
english: At the same time, under the principle of respecting the Pingpu ethnic group's self- identity, and recognizing their identity, we will examine relevant laws before September 30 of this year, so that Pingpu ethnic group identity will receive the rights and status it deserves.

ssf: thoini a kawash makthin tata wa foraz noma tata wa qali, ita alhmaza matash noma kmalawa pishfazaq goan-co-min-cok a kazakazash a proq. kataonan min-kong-fat-zin a palhkakrikriw, ita lhmaza smokos noma kmalawaiza, ya kahiza, goan-co-min-cok amin'ananak lhongqizi a inangqto, tatata wa kinangqtha mingqolhmoz akalawan. ita amabiskawoan, goan-co-min-cok a mathoaw taraan a fat mzai, "goan-co-min- cok lhongqizi ananak a fat," "goan-co-min-cok a proq noma wazaqan a fat," "goan-co-min-cok a lalawa wa fat" nomanoma, alhai sa lip-fat-inn palhkakaktha.
english: On November 1 of this year, we will begin to delineate and announce indigenous traditional territories and lands. The system of tribal public corporation is already in place. In the future, the ideals of indigenous self-government will be realized step by step. We will step up the pace and submit for legislative deliberation three laws of great importance to indigenous peoples: the Indigenous Peoples Self-Government Law, the Indigenous Peoples Land and Sea Areas Law, and the Indigenous Languages Development Law.

ssf: thoini a saqazi, yamin amingqolhmoz malhkaktha sa goan-co-min-cok palhkakrikriw a malhkaktha. isai izai a malhkaktha, cing-ho monsai thitho a palhkakrikriw a'itia manasha wa pinalhkaktha. ya kahiza, tatata kawash makashpashpat a foraz tata wa qali, hing-cing-inn amonsai mingqolhmoz a thao pishfazaq sa goan-co-min-cok a sasaz a lalawa patongkaririn thitho mzai mobalabalay, kmalawa ya shaonanantoa. adado kmalawa goan-co-min-cok a sasaz a lalawa patongkaririn, nona kmalawa sa goan-co-min-cok min'ananak lhongqizi a bangqir, hay acing-ho amakalawa monsai goan-co-nin-cok a latoro a palhkakrikriw.
english: Later this afternoon, we will convene a national indigenous peoples administrative meeting. In that meeting, the government will elaborate on the policies. On every August 1 to come, the Executive Yuan will report to the indigenous peoples our progress on restoring historical justice and transitional justice. To implement the Indigenous Peoples Basic Law, to serve indigenous historical justice, and to lay the foundation for indigenous self- government - these are the three major goals for the government's policy towards indigenous peoples.

ssf: yako thoini amalalawa inai a thao, noma izai tian- si a tanamoqtha wa goan-co-min-cok a horoy, malhintal minmriqaz a thao. malalawa yako manion alhongqizi, anto mzai malalawa manion monai amatash. malalawa yako manion goan-co-min-cok a horoy lhongqizi noma pinfazaq yakin, apariqaz cing- ho po'apaw kinalawa thitho a lalawa, dado apo'oka sa kahiwan a moririw.
english: To all of our indigenous friends here and watching on TV and online: I invite you to stand witness. I invite you not to endorse, but to oversee. Please keep pressure on the government and right its course where necessary, so that it will realize its commitments and right historical wrongs.

ssf: yako amonsai mingqolhmoz a goan-co-min- cok a horoy anoniza, manion sa pishfazaq sa itia wa thao mzai, kangqthaan ita wa proq noma kahiwan a kazakazash sa anto kaoriwan a aniamin. izai pashtay itia mara'in a shmoqrom.
english: I want to thank all of our indigenous friends. You remind everyone in this country that there is irreplaceable value in the land we tread on and the traditions we inherit. This value deserves dignity.

ssf: ita ya kahiza, amonsai cing-ho smakos inai cing- ho a palhkakrikriw, amaqa ita minalangqtha wa thao, noma az'az minalangqtha wa thao, noma inai Taiwan a proq a itia wa thao, anto amin'oka sa lalawa, anto min'oka sa rinataqan ita wa inangqto, ani mani min'aora mita wa kazakazash, niza to amiaqay isai mita wa proq min'ala'alash.
english: In the future, we will push for policies to ensure that succeeding generations of indigenous tribes and all ethnic peoples in Taiwan never lose their languages and memories, that they are never separated from their cultural traditions, and that never again are they lost in a land of their own.

ssf: amalalawa yako az'az a thao olhkiz makarishkish malhkakrikriw, mafazaq mita wa sasaz a lalawa, mafazaq mita wa proq, mafazaq mani mita wa tatata wa thao a qbit a kazakazash. az'az sa thao olhkiz mapaqaqitan, pashtay maqitan miasosoon noma pashtay mapaqaqitan, pashtay Taiwan a thao itia maqitan noma faqlho a kahiza wa ininthawan.
english: I call upon our entire society to come together and get to know our history, get to know our land, and get to know the cultures of our many ethnic peoples. Let us work towards reconciliation, a shared existence and shared prosperity, and a new future for Taiwan.

ssf: malalawa yako manion mingqolhmoz itia wa thao, isai inai maqitan a qali, pashtay ita palhintal kmalawa itia maqitan a kok-ka, kmalawa dado mariom noma mashtay manazitho a kok-ka.
english: I call upon all citizens to seize the opportunities offered by this day - to join together, work hard, and build a country of justice, a country of true diversity and equality.

ssf: pashtay maqitan piakalingkin piakaimahan. iza araiza ita.
english: Good day, everyone. Here we go.

ssf: pashtay maqitan piakalingkin piakaimahan. thoini shinshii apishfazaq pashtay manion kmoza sa akaanin a Thao a lalawa.
english: Hello, everyone, peace. Today, I am going to teach you how to say Shao for food.
Do you understand what the teacher says?

ssf: shinshii, maora iako. shdoo iho qa oqthawan malhinona?
english: I don't understand. Can you repeat it again?

ssf: ani iako tonmaza, shdoo iho piara'inin lalawa?
english: I can't hear you, can you speak louder?

ssf: riqazoan oho inai! oqtha ontal iakin malhinona motal.
english: Look here, please! Repeat after me.

ssf: oqthawan malhinona. piara'inin miho a lalawa.
english: Read it again. Please speak louder.
I forgot to bring my pen.
I forgot to bring my eraser.

ssf: shimoloan oho tatitish miho a shirshir a tataal lhmopish a horoy.
english: Please borrow erasers from your classmates.

ssf: shdoo miho a tatitish ya shimolikoan?
pananaiza lhmopish, oqthwan mapariqaz ya simaq.
english: Class dismissed, see you next week.

ssf: Hoqo a azazak iako, zain Liwan.
english: I am Shuhut's son, and my name is Quan.

ssf: iako sa Qaba wa lhopilhopishan a azazak, zain Liwan.
english: I am a student in Shuhut, my name is Quan.

ssf: kozan miho a ama wa lhanaz?
naak a ama wa lhanaz zain Hoqo.
naak a tantoqash ayozi a minlhafot thitho, zain Sholay.
english: He's my brother, his name is Taniwu.

ssf: thitho a lhanaz zain Hoqo qa?
oa, thitho a lhanaz zain Hoqo.
thitho a lhanaz zain Qaba qa?
ani, thitho a lhanaz zain Sholay.
Apin thitho. naak a pan'inaan thitho.
naak a horoy thitho, thitho a lhanaz zain Ishoz.
english: She is my friend, her name is Ishuz.

ssf: pizaiza s miho a qamishan thoini?
iako thoini a kawash makthin a qamishan.
pizaiza s thitho a qamishan thoini?
thitho thoini a kawash makthin tosha wa qamishan.
pizaiza s miho a ama wa qamishan thoini?
naak a ama thoini a kawash marimaz a qamishan.

english: How many brothers and sisters do you have?

ssf: itia naak a latosha tantoqash a minlhafot noma itia latata shashoazi a minlhafot.
english: I have two brothers and sisters and one younger brother and sister.

ssf: itia miho a tantoqash ayozi a minlhafot?
ani, oka sa naak a tantoqash a ayozi.
english: No, I don't have a brother.

ssf: lapiza wa thao manion tata wa taon?
english: How many people are in your family?

ssf: iamin tata wa taon lashpaat a thao.
english: There are four of us in our family.
I study at a head society.

ssf: noma s palhkakrikriw miho a pan'amaan?
english: What does your uncle do for a living?

ssf: naak a tantoqash binanao'az a minlhafot thitho.
itia palhkakrikriw miho a tantoqash binanao'az a minlhafot?
english: Does your sister have a job?

ssf: itosi thitho mriqariqaz shiz a taon malhkakrikriw.
minlhafot thaithoy qa latosha wa thao?

english: Yes, I'm from the Thao tribe.

ssf: miniahala inai a thao miho a binanao'az qa?
oa, marotarotaw naak a tata wa taon a thao.
english: Yes, we are all very tall.

ssf: miho a shashoazi binanao'az a minlhafot lhmopishiza thitho qa?
english: Does your sister go to school?

ssf: mafazaq malhinona Thao a lalawa qa miho a shashoazi a minlhafot?
english: Do your siblings speak the language?

ssf: oa, mafazaq thaithoy malhinona Thao a lalawa.
english: Yes, they speak the ethnic language.
I have three brothers and sisters.

ssf: miasoon oho miho a ama ina qa?
english: Do you live with your parents?

ssf: oa, miasoon iako naak a ama ina.
english: Yes, I live with my mom and dad.

ssf: miasoon oho miho a apora'in apoki'ay qa?
english: Do you live with your grandparents?

ssf: ani, ani iako to miasoon thaithoy.
english: No, I didn't live with them.

ssf: miasoon iako naak a ama ina noma tantoqash ayozi a minlhafot.
english: I live with my father, mother and brother.
I come from the tribe of Idashor.
Our home is in the Idaho tribe.
My hometown is in Sun Moon Lake.

ssf: alhakaiza iho moshoqish miho a kataonan?
english: When are you going back to the tribe?

ssf: miaqay iako motaon ya pinangqaiza mahnariza wa qali.
english: I will go back in the summer.

ssf: mo'apawiza sa tilhaz, mathoaw mahnar sa qali.
english: The sun is coming out, it's very hot.
Is it going to be cold outside?
It's cold, so wear more clothes.

ssf: dara wa mahnar thoini a qali, mathoaw taodoo.
english: It's neither cold nor hot today, very comfortable.

ssf: maqitan sa thoini a tanlhoan a qali qa?
qali oka sa orom, mo'apawiza sa kilhpoz.
english: There were no clouds in the sky; the stars came out.

ssf: maqitan ya isaran a qali qa?
mokaktoniza qmosaz, mo'apawiza sa tilhaz noma mo'apawiza mani sa qariwazwaz.
english: The rain has just stopped, the sun has come out, the rainbow is coming out.
What's the weather like where you are?

ssf: inai iamin mathoaw mara'in a fari.
english: We're going to have a big storm here.

ssf: mathoaw maqitan, mathoaw matata wa tilhaz.
english: Very well, out of the big sun.
I have to go to school.

ssf: qali mathoaw mashimzaw, apashinasha sa holos.
english: The weather is very cold, so wear more clothes.

ssf: a'ontarawin sa qosaz ya ikahi, ata iho to in'aora katho sa pashikan.
english: It's going to rain heavily, don't forget to bring an umbrella.

ssf: tminobaromboniza to ikahi, amaqosaz painan ya ikahi.
english: It just thundered, and it might rain later.

ssf: qminosaz to ikahi, pangqaiza qosaz thoini.
english: It just rained, and now it's stopped.

ssf: qminosaz painan to ikahi, matobo sa saran.
english: It seems to have rained and the road is wet.

ssf: qosaziniza? mino matoboiza sa miho a boot?
english: Is it raining? Why are you all wet?

ssf: qosazin isaran, ani iako to kminatho s pashikan.
english: It's raining outside, so I didn't bring an umbrella.

ssf: mathoaw mara'in sa fari noma naak a ponoq infarin mathoaw makashpar.
english: The wind is blowing so hard that my head hurts.

ssf: mathoaw mahaha sa tilhaz noma naak a ponoq patilhazin mathoaw mingqaqarimozmoz.
english: The sun is so big, it makes me dizzy.
I forgot to bring my pen.
I forgot to bring my chopsticks.

ssf: min'aora iako mani kmatho sa kakthi, osha ita fariw.
english: I also forgot to bring my chopsticks, let's go buy them.
Let's go buy a pen, shall we?
Well, I still have to buy erasers.

ssf: izao! fariw ita konshashano a akaanin?
english: Come on! Let's go get breakfast, shall we?
No, I've already eaten at home.
I forgot to heat up my lunchbox.
I forgot to bring my lunchbox.

ssf: konsoon ita kmaan sa naak a pinoqafay!
english: Then let's eat my lunch box together!

ssf: noma sa akaanin oho ya saqazi?
english: What are you having for lunch?

ssf: amakaan iako lhopilhopishan a taon a konsaqazi a akaanin.
english: I want a nutritious school lunch.

ssf: thoini iako kminatho sa pinoqafay, konsoon ita saqazi kmaan.
english: I've brought a lunchbox today, let's eat together at noon!

ssf: izao! oshaiza ita matinhina sa qarimosoz?
english: Come on! Let's go play basketball, shall we?

ssf: izao! oshaiza ita matinhina sa paro sa qarimosoz?
arawan oho sa thathapo lhai iakin.
oa, haya wa thathapo lhai ihon.
english: Okay, here's a broomstick for you.

ssf: arawan oho sa tatitish lhai iakin?
english: Can you help me with the cloth?

ssf: mathapo iako bokhaz, palalawan oho Toba mara sa tatitish.
english: I was sweeping the floor and you asked Tuba to help you with the cloth.
Have you finished sweeping the floor?

ssf: mino iho qa anto mathapo sa bokhaz.

english: The floor is dirty, go clean it.
Okay, I'll go get the cloth.

ssf: mathoaw maradaradaq hoya wa paziwat, titishiwan oho!
english: That window is very dirty, go clean it.

ssf: italhawan, inai niwan iako to okaktonin mathapo.
english: Wait a minute, I'm not done sweeping here yet.

ssf: amakilhim iako sa foifoilh patashan a shinshii.
english: I'm going to see my teacher.
What do you do after school?

ssf: amososoon iako naak a horoy maqaqoyash.
english: I'm going to sing with my friends.
Where does he go after school?
May I ask if Tumi is home?
She's at home, please come in.
May I ask if Tumi is home? *[Lisin] Please change the name to an ethnic woman.

ssf: oka thitho itaon, noma sa akalawan oho qa?
english: She's not here, what can I do for you?

ssf: apora'in, iako Poni, tanaiwan sa pitaw.
english: Grandpa, I'm Puni, please open the door.

ssf: Apin, Sihaw iako, kilhim iako ihon amapalhalhiqash.
english: Apin, I'm Sihaw, I've come to play with you. *[Kacaw][Mayaw] Please change the names of the women of each tribe.

ssf: oa, mathoaw iako mangqtoqto ihon. iahiaw motaon mapalhinona!
english: Yeah! I miss you so much. Come on, let's chat!
Please sit down and have some tea.

ssf: oao~ mathoaw manion a poshawil makanshoz maqitan iqilhaan.
oa! haya wa ribosh a bonlhaz mathoaw taodoo ya riqazan.
maqitan kaanin qa ribosh a bonlhaz?
pinintataiza ina kontanlhoan a pania'an iahiaw monai kmaan!
english: Mom has cooked dinner, come and eat!
Okay, I'll go wash my hands.

ssf: kaanoan! ata to kayaw! anto iho sa shahitan.
english: Eat! Don't be shy! You're not an outsider.
I ate a lot, I'm full.
I have to leave now, see you next time.

ssf: oa, onaiwan iho naak a taon kilhnaqoalh ya ishawanan.
english: Okay, come to my house sometime.

ssf: pashtay piakalingkin piakaimahan, palhintal ita thoini mosoi kataonan makikalhi apo nomanoma.
english: Good health and peace to all, today we will go to the tribe to interview the elders.

ssf: apo Kilash, itiza iamin monai mriqaz ihon.
english: Grandpa Kilash, we've come to see you.

ssf: ba, mafazaq manion mashthao! mathoaw maqitan!
english: You guys speak Thau! That's great!

ssf: pashtay piakalingkin piakaimahan, palhintal ita thoini mosoi tamakoan mobohat.
english: Be healthy and safe everyone, today we are going to work in the vegetable garden together.

ssf: pashtay oniawan ododor, ata to in'aora kmatho sa obohat a aniamin.
english: Come and line up, remember to bring your tools.

ssf: oa, shinshii, kminatho iamin az'az a obohat a aniamin.
english: Yes, sir, we've got our tools.
Not yet, it's still far away.

ssf: oshaiza iho mara sa romfaz a madanshir.
english: You go get the bird catcher.
Okay, I'll go and catch the birds.

ssf: pashtay piakalingkin piakaimahan, amotosi ita thoini ia'ianan nomanoma wa lhkaribosh a lolooman.
english: Be healthy and safe, we are going to the zoo today.

ssf: mathoaw maqitan! amiakoza ita ya motanto?
english: Awesome! How are we going to get there?

ssf: pashtay ododor, afariw ita sa qahil.
english: Everyone line up, we need to buy tickets now.

ssf: romfaz itanamoqtha noma qlhoran itanarikos, shanamanion mriqaz.
english: There are birds in the front and snakes in the back.

ssf: ata to shkash, oshaiza iho riqazoan sa romfaz.
english: Don't be afraid, then you go and see the birds.

ssf: ya tata wa tilhaz amoshoqish ita moriot miasoon.
english: We'll be back in an hour.

ssf: noma sa minriqaz iho qa thoini?
minriqaz iako sa manasha wa qlhoran noma itiawan sa manasha wa romfaz.
english: I saw a lot of snakes and a lot of birds.
Hurry up, we have to go.

ssf: italhawan iakin, mathoaw mingkashlay naak a koskos.
english: Wait for me, my feet are tired.
Shall we go swimming at the pool together?

ssf: mathoaw inai manasha wa thao mraoz.
english: There are a lot of people swimming here.

ssf: mathoaw maroqroq imangkathi kinai ita mraoz shdooiza.
english: The water is deep there, so we just swim here.

ssf: noma wa barimbin ilhongqoan oho monai?
english: What kind of car did you take?

ssf: miakoza iho motosi mriqariqaz shiz a taon?
english: How did you get to the hospital?

ssf: naak a ama pombarimbin iakin malhintal motanto.
amiakoza thitho miaqay ya amotosi lhopilhopishan a taon?
english: How does he usually go to school?

ssf: milhongqo thitho mabiskaw a barimbin ya motosi lhopilhopishan a taon.
english: He took the subway to school.

ssf: miakoza miho a apoki'ay ya motosi fariw sa shanglaw?
english: How does your grandmother go to the grocery store?

ssf: matong'oto-bai thitho ya motosi fariw sa shanglaw.
english: She went to the grocery store on a motorcycle.
How are you going to get to LaRue?
I'm taking a boat to LaRue.
Why is he going to Japan?

ssf: milhongqo thitho sa marfazfaz a barimbin motosi Lit-poon.
english: He took a plane to Japan.

ssf: noma wa barimbin ya ilhongqoan thitho ya motosi Kao-shiong?
english: What bus did he take to Kaohsiung?

ssf: milhongqo thitho sa mabiskaw maqoliosh a barimbin motosi Kao-shiong.
english: He took the THSR to Kaohsiung.

ssf: kazaiko thitho milhongqo sa apoy a barimbin motosi Tai-taang?
english: Did he take a train to Taitung?

ssf: oa, milhongqo thitho apoy a barimbin motosi Tai-taang
english: Yes, he took a train to Taitung.

ssf: ani, milhongqo thitho marfazfaz a barimbin motosi Tai-taang.
english: No, he took a plane to Taitung.

ssf: itia qa ia'ianan milhongqo sa ba-so iqoalh?
english: Is there a bus stop near here?

ssf: itia, ialonlondoz oho monsai saran shdooiza mriqaz sa ia'ianan milhongqo sa ba-so itanamoqtha.
english: Yes, you can see the bus standing in front of you if you go straight down this road.

ssf: intoa s ya iqoalh inai a ia'ianan milhongqo sa mabiskaw a barimbin?
english: Where is the nearest MRT station?

ssf: oka inai sa ia'ianan milhongqo sa mabiskaw a barimbin, moqay iho shdoo milhongqo sa shadonan a barimbin.
english: There is no MRT station here, you can only take a taxi.

ssf: alhakaiza shaonatanto lhopilhopishan a taon ya milhongqo sa ba-so?
english: How long will it take to get to the school if I take the bus?

ssf: makthin rima wa qombo ashaonatanto lhopilhopishan a taon.
alhakaiza shaonatanto Tai-tioong ya milhongqo sa mabiskaw maqoliosh a barimbin?
english: How long will it take to get to Taichung if I take the THSR?
I will come to Taichung in an hour.

ssf: amindaaq qa ya pombarimbin amotosi U-lai?
english: Is it a long drive to Ulai?

ssf: alhakaiza shaonatanto naak a taon ya milhongqo sa mabiskaw a barimbin?
english: How long did it take you to come to my house by subway?

ssf: mafazaq iho qa kmangqtha sa kangqthaan a barimbin?
english: Do you know how to ride a bicycle?

ssf: mafazaq iako kmangqtha sa kangqthaan a barimbin.

english: No, I don't have a motorcycle.
Don't, I don't know much about it.

ssf: ishawanan oho ya saqazi? amotanto iako makikalhiwan ihon, shdoo?
english: Are you free this afternoon? I'd like to visit you, is that okay?
Okay, I'll wait for you at home.

ssf: ishawanan oho ya simaq? amakikalhi iako ihon Thao a kahiwan a lalawa.
english: Are you free tomorrow? I'd like to ask you about the Thao legends.

ssf: amotosi iako hodon ya simaq, oka iako itaon.
english: I'm going to the mountains tomorrow, so I won't be home.

ssf: tomaza iako soma wa thao, mathoaw iho mafazaq Thao a kazakazash, amakikalhi iako ihon.
english: I have heard that you know a lot about Thao traditions and customs and I would like to ask you a few questions.

ssf: anto iako to la mafazaq, kanoiza ashontam iako ihon ya mafazaq iako.
english: I don't know much about it, but I will try to answer as best I can.

ssf: makikalhiwan iako ihon shdoo ya polaonin sa bahi? ya miazitho, apidazah polin sa thao.
english: Can I record the video? It will be easier to record in the future.

ssf: makatanatho makthin ianan makashpashpat sa naak a qamishan.
miho a binanao'az mani sa Thao qa?
english: Is your wife also a Thao?

ssf: noma s lalawa ya kafazaqin oho?
mafazaq iako mashthao a lalawa noma mashshpoot a lalawa.
mathoaw iako ma'alah'a thoini shdoo makikalhi ihon, palhinonawan oho ya moribosh a parshian, shdoo qa?
english: It's a pleasure to interview you today, can you talk about the taboo of hunting?

ssf: oa. miaqay iako mototosi hodon moribosh to parhawayoan.
english: Yes. I used to go hunting in the mountains when I was young.

ssf: anoniza, pishfazaq iho iakin thoini mathoaw maqitan.
english: Thank you, what you taught me today was really great.

ssf: iako inzai a lalawa az'az modoo, tanatoqash inkahiwan a pinalhinona.
english: All that I say is true, the sayings of my ancestors.

ssf: pananaiza thoini a lalawa. mathoaw anoniza foifoilh iho iakin.
english: That's all for today's interview. Thank you very much for sharing with us.

ssf: anonin qa! amoqtha ita mapalhinona ya kahiza.
amoshaiza iako, mathoaw iako miko tonmaza soma wa kahiwan a lalawa ya kahiza.
english: I'm leaving now, I look forward to hearing more stories next time.

ssf: maqitan iho, noma s afariwin oho?
english: Hello, what do you want to buy?
I want to buy a cup.

ssf: maqitan iho, noma s afariwin oho?
english: Hello, what are you looking for?
I want to buy a hat.

ssf: afariw iako baroko, itia manion baroko afariwin?
english: I want to buy a cup, do you sell them?
Yes, how many do you want to buy?
No, we don't sell betel nut.
How many packs do you want to buy?

ssf: ananaiwan iakin toro a pinotiqo a zashoq.

english: I want to buy sweet potatoes.
All the sweet potatoes are sold out.
I want to buy two bottles of oil.
We only have one bottle left.
You go and buy me eggs.
How many pounds do you want to buy?

ssf: lapiza wa tingting a qarithoy afariwin oho?
english: How many pounds of eggs do you want to buy?
I want to buy two catties.

ssf: afariw iako latosha finotolh a shanglaw.
english: I want to buy two handfuls of vegetables.

ssf: inai moqayza tininashan latoro finotolh a shanglaw, polhthkiz lhai ihon.
english: There are three handfuls of vegetables left, all for you!

ssf: lakoza wa toali haya pinotiqo a zashoq?
english: How much is this bag of rice?

ssf: tosha shaba tata wa pinotiqo a zashoq.
english: 200 Yuan for a packet of rice.

ssf: shoqolhmozin maposhaz tata wa soi, shdooiza ya maposhaz a soi.
makatanatho makthin rima wa soi inai.
amoqtha iako fariw ladado, mintata shaba wa soi.
english: I'll buy some more, and make up 100 yuan.

ssf: shoqolhmozin larima shaba ianan makthin a soi.
mathoaw maklis izai, shdoo pot'oka ladado qa?
english: It's too expensive, can you make it cheaper?
No, this is already very cheap.
I want to buy this packet of cookies.

ssf: matoroz a soi haya madahon, soma wa aniamin afariwin oho?
english: $30 for the cookies, anything else you need?

ssf: shdoo miho a toali ya shimolikoan?
min'aora iako kminatho sa toali, shdoo miho a toali ya shimolikoan?
english: I forgot to bring the money, can I borrow your money?

ssf: min'aora iako mani kmatho sa toali!
english: I don't have any money either!

ssf: ani, mihalawan iho shminimol sa naak a toali, niwan iho to rinirian.
english: No, you haven't paid me back the money you borrowed last time.

ssf: shdoo miho a holos ya shimolikoan?
shdoo iako amashimol miho a patashan?
naak a patashan shimolin sa Ilon.
english: My book was borrowed by Ilun.

ssf: shimolikoan miho a kangqthaan a barimbin?
english: Can I borrow your bicycle, please?
Okay, but you have to give it back to me tomorrow.

ssf: qosaziniza, ani iako to kminatho pashikan, shdoo miho a pashikan ya shimolikoan?
english: It's raining, I don't have an umbrella, can you lend me one?

ssf: moqay naak a pashikan latata, iasoon ita!
english: I only have an umbrella, let's stick together!

ssf: haya patashan shinimol iho iakin, ariri ihon.
english: This is the book you borrowed from me last time, I give it back to you.

ssf: noma wa patashan iho ya amariqaz shdoo foilh iakin.
english: You can tell me what else you want to read.

ssf: alhakaiza ya mriri iako ihon sa toali?
english: When do I have to pay you back?

ssf: anonin qa! iho ya itia sa toali ariri iakin.
english: It's okay, you can pay me back when you have the money.

ssf: shinimimol naak a toali, alhakaiza aposhoqishin oho?
english: When are you going to pay me back?
I'll return it to you tomorrow.

ssf: shinimimol naak a patashan, alhakaiza aposhoqishin oho?
english: When are you going to return my book?
Didn't I return your book yesterday?

ssf: haya patatash ti Toba shimolin oho?
english: Did Tuba lend you this pen?

ssf: oa, shinimol iako a patatash thoini.
english: Yes, I borrowed it from him today.

ssf: haya patatash shinimol iho ti Toba qa?
