english: I want some eggs too, do you have some?

ssf: naam a qarithoy olhthkizin soma wa finariw.

english: I want to buy some clothes.
What kind of clothes do you like?

ssf: afariw iako loish a rima wa holos.
english: I want to buy the clothes with short sleeves.

ssf: qazii ya miakoza s izai maqolhaqolha?
qazii ya itiawan soma wa kinasia?
iamin itiawan sa mapozipozi noma madishlom.
english: We have white and blue ones too.

ssf: ananaiwan iakin tata wa madishlom a holos.
english: Please give me the clothes in blue.

ssf: Qabos shintoa iho to ikahi? shitosi iho pinkazakaza sa boot?
english: Qabus, where have you been just now? Did you go exercising?

ssf: ani, shitosi iako mindahip apoki'ay fariwin sa shanglaw.
english: No, I went grocery shopping for my grandma.

ssf: iho ya ishawanan ya mahomhom? qazii ya mat iakin kmaan afo.
english: No wonder! Are you available at night? Would you like to have a meal with me?
No, I want to buy some clothes.
Then, I will go with you.

ssf: maqitan iho, lakoza wa toali haya wa finotolh a shanglaw.
english: Hello, how much is this bunch of vegetables?

ssf: tata wa finotolh a shanglaw maposhaz soi.
english: The vegetables are $20 for a bunch.

ssf: lakoza wa toali haya wa bona?
english: How much are these sweet potatoes?

ssf: tata tingting a bona matoroz soi.
english: Sweet potatoes are thirty dollars for a pound.

ssf: ananaiwan iakin tosha finotolh a shanglaw noma tata tingting a bona.
english: Please give me two bunches of vegetables and a pound of sweet potatoes.

ssf: Toba, min'aora iako kminatho sa patatash, shdoo iho shimolikoan?
english: Tuba, I forgot to bring my pen. Can you lend me one?

ssf: oka iako mani, ti Shoni izai.
english: I don't have one either. This is Shuni's.

ssf: shdoo ya shimolikoan? mohiaw iako poshoqishin oho.
english: Can you lend me the pen for a second? I will return to you immediately.
Thank you and thank Shuni for me.

ssf: aposhoqishin iako sa izai a latosha wa patashan.
english: I want to return these two books.
No problem and what else do you need?

ssf: amoqthawan iako shmimol latoro a patashan.
english: I would like to borrow these three books.

ssf: shdooiza, ata to in'aoraan ya toroiza wa qali aposhoqishin.
english: Sure and remember to return them after three days.

ssf: niwan iho to poshoqishin iakin tatitish.
english: You haven't returned me the eraser.
Then, why is my eraser missing?
Did you lend it to Tuba?
I don't know. I will go and ask her.

ssf: mihala iako shimolin naak a tatitish ihon.
english: I will lend you my eraser first.

ssf: Shoni, izai a maka'apaw a holos sa Toba wa shimolin oho?
english: Shuni, did Tuba lend you this coat?

ssf: ani, haya naak a ina finariw lhai iakin.
english: No, my mom bought it for me.

ssf: Toba wa maka'apaw a holos tataal miho.
english: Tuba's coat is the same as yours.

ssf: thitho a maka'apaw a holos maqosoqosom, anto tataal iamin.
english: 's coat is thHis coat is black, so our colors are different.e same as yours.

ssf: Shoni, shinimol iho sa Hodon a toali?
english: Shuni, did you borrow money from Hudun?

ssf: oa, naor thoini iako mriri thitho, min'aora iako makatho sa toali.
english: Yes, I was supposed to return to him today, but I forgot to bring the money.
Then, when will you return the money?
I will return to him tomorrow.
Okay, I will tell Hudun for you.

ssf: ya smapok sa mashmash apasain sa qadop, noma ya smapok sa tikolhath apasain sa mahaqo, ya miazitho mobalabalay.
english: It is correct to catch mice through rangay and catch bamboo partridges through qjiulang.

ssf: naor ya miazitho, moririw to soma iako, amaqa iako anto mara.
english: No wonder! I am mistaken and that's why I cannot catch any of them.

ssf: pinfazaq iako ihon amiakoza kmalawa s izai latosha wa toqris.
english: Then I will teach you how to set up these two traps.

ssf: oa! maqitan, ya miazitho shdoo iako mara sa lhkaribosh ya kahiza.
english: Great! I will be able to catch the prey in the future.

ssf: bohat a lhmir mathoaw marotawiza, osoiwan oho thapa mara sa kaklhit, amotosi ita bohat.
english: The grass in the fields is too tall. Go to the warehouse to take the sickle and let's go to the fields.

ssf: isai lhalhahi a shirshir, makontanto iho thapa ashaqtoniza.
english: Beside the back basket, you will see it when you enter the warehouse.

ssf: inanoro ya mara ata to klhitin, mathoaw kaklhit malamlam.
english: Be careful and don't get hurt. The sickle is very sharp.

ssf: ata to kangqthaan naak a toqris.
naak a toqris isai hoya wa ribosh a bangqir.
english: My trap is under that tree.

ssf: pinataqal iako izai, mafazaq iako naak a toqris ya intoa.
english: I make a mark here, so I know where my trap is.

ssf: haya wa lhalhozo, polhalhozo iamin falhaza wa shirshir smapok sa rosaw.
english: This is a fish trap which we put beside the river for fishing.

ssf: oka iamin lhalhozo, pasain iamin paniza ya maniza sa rosaw.
english: We don't have any fish traps there, so we catch fish with a fishing rod.

ssf: iako anto pinasa paniza, shdoo iho soma wa qali pinfazaq iakin?
english: I have never used a fishing rod before, would you mind teaching me next time?

ssf: oa! soma wa qali apalhintaz ita mosoi maniza sa rosaw.
english: Sure! Let's go fishing together next time.

ssf: ya soma wa qali apinfazaq iako ihon kmalawa sa lhalhozo.
english: I will teach you how to make a fish trap next time.

ssf: makakakri miho a paniza, qazii ya mopaniza sa rosaw, iahiaw shmoroz iho.
english: Your fishing rod is moving. Isn't the fish on the hook? Pull it up!

ssf: italhawan, ma'a'a'inor sa roza, inai iako shmoroz sa paniza, otosiwan oho mara sa dawaz.
english: Wait, the ship is rolling heavily. I am here to pull the fishing rod and you should go there to grab me the net.

ssf: shoroz iho sa rosaw pakonanai, shorozikoan sa rosaw.
english: Pull the fish to my side and I will help you pull it up.

ssf: mathoaw maqitan! o'araan manasha sa rosaw thoini, mathoaw maponishiza loloman sa rosaw.
english: Great! It is a bumper crop today with full fish baskets.
Let's go back immediately and share it with everyone.

ssf: itiza foifoilh patashan a shinshii monai.
ingqaiza malhalhiqash, iahiaw oshai miho a pangka milhongqo.
english: Stop playing and quickly sit in your seat.

ssf: ripay rima thoini, pangqaiza simaq, mosoon ita kilhnaqoalh!
english: It's Friday today, we have a day off tomorrow. Let's go out and play together!
Great! Let's go to the riverside.
What day will it be tomorrow?

ssf: ripay toro simaq, mosoon ita matinhina sa maqarimosoz ya simaq saqazi!
english: Tomorrow will be Wednesday. Let's go play ball tomorrow afternoon!

ssf: noma s kalawan oho simaq a shashano?
english: What will you be doing tomorrow morning?

ssf: amontal iako naak a ina, motosi balinoqaz a taon.
english: Tomorrow will be Sunday, I will be going to church with my mom.
I feel like vomiting. I need to go to the restroom.

ssf: shinshii, makashpar naak a tiaz, amotosiwak pothaqian.
english: Teacher, I have a stomachache. I need to go to the restroom.

ssf: qazii iako mosoi mashinaw rima qa?
english: May I go wash my hands?
It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.

ssf: shinshii, mathoaw makashpar naak a ponoq, apangqawak ya saqazi.
english: It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.
Okay, take care and go home.

ssf: shinshii, apangqawak ya ripay tata, maqa amariqaz iako mriqariqaz shiz a shinshii.
english: Teacher, I need to take a sick leave next Monday. I have to see a doctor.

ssf: oa, piakakalinkin s miho a boot.
makashpar thitho tiaz, itosi thitho sa pothaqian.
english: She has a stomachache. She's in the restroom.

ssf: shinshii, makashpar Shohot a laholaho, pangqa thoini.
english: Teacher, Shuhut has a sore throat. She took a sick leave today.

ssf: in'ananak oho mzai miho a nomanoma.
naak a lhanaz zain Qaba Lhkapamomo, iako thoini makthin a qamishan.
english: My name is Qaba Lhkapamumu, and I'm 10 years old.

ssf: naak a lhanaz zain Qaba Lhkapamomo.

english: What ethnic group are you from?

ssf: miho a taon az'az miniahala inai a thao qa?
english: Are all your family members indigenous?

ssf: oa, iamin tata taon az'az Thao.
english: Yes, my whole family is Thau.

ssf: ani, to Thao naak a ama, noma Shpoot naak a ina.
english: No, my father is Thau, and my mother is Han Taiwanese.

ssf: hoya miho a ama qa? pizaiza thitho a qamishan?
english: Is that your father? How old is he?

ssf: ani, naam a kataonan a tanatoqash, makashpashpatiza makthin thitho a qamishan.
english: No, he is an elder of our tribe. He is 80 years old.

ssf: pizaiza s miho a tantoqash ayozi a minlhafot a qamishan?
makthin makashpashpat naak a tantoqash ayozi a minlhafot a qamishan.
miho a tantoqash ayozi a minlhafot manasha qamishan mat iho qa?
english: Is your brother much older than you?

ssf: tata shaba mashpatiz shian a rotaw iako.
mindaaq iako anto mriqaz ihon, minrotawiza iho qa?
english: I haven't seen you in a while. Have you grown taller?

ssf: oa, tata shaba matoroziza shian a rotaw iako.
oa, matoroziza iako qong tingting thoini.
amotosi iako palhkakrikriw a ianan makilhim iako foifoilh patashan a shinshii.
english: I'm going to the office to see the teacher.
He's going to throw away the trash.

ssf: itosi thitho mraoz a proq, amalantatnor thitho mraoz ya ikahi.
english: He's at the swimming pool. He's going to compete in a swimming competition later.

ssf: intoa sa Ilon? amalantatnor thitho malalia ya ikahi.
english: Where is Ilun? She's going to compete in a running competition later.

ssf: itosi thitho palhkakrikriw a ianan, amotanto iako malalawa.
english: She's in the auditorium. I'll go call her.

ssf: palhintal ita motanto makakakri a danshiqan.
english: Let's go to the playground together.

ssf: amihala iako fariw sa konsaqazi a akaanin, amotanto iako makilhim iho ya ikahi.
english: I'll go buy lunch first, and then I'll meet you later.

ssf: izao osoon ita mongqibi sa pinoqafay!
english: Let's carry the lunch boxes together!

ssf: kilhimoan oho soma, amotosi iako makilhim foifoilh patashan a shinshii.
english: You find someone else, I'm going to find the teacher.
Is Quan competing in running today?
No, he's competing in high jump.

ssf: amalantatnor iho nomanoma qa ya amalantatnor nomanoma wa qali?
english: Will you compete in the sports day?

ssf: noma s kalawan ita ya amalantatnor nomanoma wa qali?
english: What will we do in the sports day?
We will compete in tug of war.

ssf: afariwin soma ita akaanin ya amalantatnor nomanoma wa qali qa?
english: Will we sell food at the sports day?

ssf: ani, afariwin soma ita marfazfaz a maqarimosoz.

english: Congratulations on getting first place! You're amazing!
Yes, she's sleeping in her room.

ssf: oka itaon, mosaran thitho to ikahi, amotaon thitho ya tanlhoan.
english: No, she's not. She just went out and will be back in the evening.

ssf: isoi makinposhaz a taon thitho, anasaya iho makinposhaz a taon kmilhim thitho.
english: He's upstairs. You can go up and find him.

ssf: ba! Malihan, mathoaw mataliza anto mriqaz ihon, maqitan iho qa?
english: It's Malihan. I haven't seen you in a while! How have you been?
I'm doing great! I came to chat with you.

ssf: isa ainoz kmal'in thitho sa pania'an, apalalawak.
english: He's in the kitchen cooking. Let me go call him.

ssf: motosi thitho qalhofo smapok sa ranaw.
english: She went to the chicken coop to catch chickens.

ssf: oka manion a apora'in itaon, isai bohat thitho, itaon manion mitalha thitho.
english: Your grandfather is not at home. He's in the field. Wait for him to come back.

ssf: mathoaw mataliza anto mriqaz ihon, minmarotawiza iho.
english: I haven't seen you in a while. You've grown taller.

ssf: mathoaw maqaran naak a shnaw ya mriqaz ihon.
english: It's so good to see you.

ssf: haya wa ong-lai pansha manion, apisai matithi a kakado.
english: Here's a pineapple for you. Put it in the refrigerator.

ssf: mindaaqiza anto shinai, amalalawa iako thaithoy pashtay molhthkiz monai makaan.
english: It's been a while. Let's have a meal together.

ssf: ingqaiza oka shawashawan, oqay iako miqilha poshawil, osoi ita maharan a bokhaz malhalhinona.
english: No need to bother. I'll just have tea. Let's sit in the living room and chat.

ssf: anoniza! ingqaiza oka shawashawan, amotaon iako.
english: Thank you for your hospitality. I have to go now.

ssf: kinapathay iako haya ranaw, kathoiza iho manataon makaan.
english: This chicken was just freshly killed. Take it home and enjoy it slowly.

ssf: qazii ya simaq a saqazi mapariqaz ita?
english: Can I make an appointment with you tomorrow afternoon?

ssf: isoi ita lhopilhopishan a taon mitalha? apashtiroq iamin.
english: How about meeting at school? We need to shoot a video.

ssf: osoi ita talhoqan mitalha maqitan, a'ifazin Thao a holos iako motanto.
english: Then let's go to the community center. I'll wear folk costume.

ssf: mathoaw lamaqitan iamin a sa-ko-laa ya makabokay. ya makabokay onai iho makilhim iakin.
english: The cherry blossoms in our tribe are beautiful when they bloom. Come find me when the flowers bloom!

ssf: ashaonatosiza pohoboqiza wa qali, mathoaw mindaaq!
english: That would have to wait until spring. It's too late, isn't it?

ssf: qazii ya Tongkariri Los'an iho monai!
english: Then come during our Tungkariri Lus'an!
Alright! I'm looking forward to it!
May I ask why you decided to move back to the tribe?
I want to return to teach at the local school.

ssf: mino iho qa anto itosi mawalhnaq a proq foifoilh patashan?
english: Why not teach in the city?

ssf: maqa mangqto iako naak a kataonan a proq, noma miko iako lhongqizi kataonan a thao.
english: Because I miss my hometown and I also want to give back to the tribe.

ssf: mathoaw ma'ania iho tonoon, tima foilh ihon?
english: You're very skilled at weaving, who taught you?

ssf: naak a apoki'ay, lamathoaw thitho ma'ania tonoon maqosom a tanatoqash isa naam a kataonan.
english: It was my grandmother, she is the most skilled weaver in our tribe.

ssf: mino iho qa amangqto minfazaq tonoon sa maqosom?
english: How did you develop an interest in learning weaving?

ssf: maqa tonoon sa maqosom mita wa kazakazash, mangqto iako izai a kazakazash ata po'okai.
english: Weaving is a part of our culture, and I want to ensure its continuity.

ssf: haya sonda wa qilha mathoaw maqitan ya qilhan.
mathoaw ma'ania iho, amindaaq ya kmalawa haya qilha?
english: You're really talented. Does it take a long time to make?

ssf: anto mindaaq, tata wa ripay painan aminqilhaiza. pintatan sonda wa zashoq masa kamar, noma pahiboran sa bolbol, noma riboqin pisai qatapay, noma posai sa tahamish.
english: No, it only takes about a week. After steaming the sticky rice and white rice, we mix it with yeast powder, and then it can be stored in a jar.

ssf: itia haya makamon noma tilkon, iako min'ananak malhoiza!
english: I have chili and lokiy, both grown by myself!

ssf: lakoza wa toali haya latosha afariwik?
molhthkiz lhopishin tosha shaba ianan larima makthin a soi.
moshnaw iako haya holos, lapiza wa toali?
english: I like this piece of clothing. How much is it?

ssf: haya latata larima shaba wa soi.

english: It's too expensive. Can't you lower the price a bit?

ssf: ata, ya ladado pongqalath iako sa toali.
english: No, if I lower it further, I'll lose money.

ssf: shdoo! afariw iako latata maqosoqosom a holos.
english: Alright then, I'll take a black piece of clothing.

ssf: afariw iako haya fonosh noma qashay.
english: I want this knife and this pot.

ssf: molhthkiz lhopishin latosha matilatilaw a soi, haya fonosh noma qashay min'ananak iako kmalawa, amathoaw mindaaq maqitan kinalawa.
english: It's a total of 2000 dollars. I handmade these, and they are guaranteed to last a long time.

ssf: amalalawa iako naak a horoy monai fariw, pot'ladadoan dai?
english: I'll introduce my friend to buy. Can you give a further discount?
Alright! I'll give you a discount.

ssf: izao onai mariqazoan! farifariw holos noma tamohon!
english: Come and take a look! We sell clothes and hats.

ssf: lapiza wa toali haya wa holos?
haya latata holos toro shaba ianan marimaz a soi, noma ya latoro shdooiza tata matilatilaw a soi.
english: One piece of clothing is 350 dollars, three pieces for 1000 dollars.

ssf: amoqay iako fariw latata, anai faqlho a holos
english: I'll just buy one piece, please give me a new one.

ssf: maqitan iho, afariw iako sonda wa afo noma qana.
english: Hello, I would like to buy sticky rice and braised pork with maqaw pepper.

ssf: molhthkizin fariwiniza s afo okaiza. itia tatanaq a qmo, afariw iho?
english: The rice is sold out. I have tana mochi, would you like to buy them?

ssf: oa! fariw iako tata, amoqthaiza iako monai fariw afo.
english: Alright, please give me one. I'll come back next time to buy rice.

ssf: oa, apasain qahil iako potiqo lhai ihon, haya marimaz a soi.
english: Okay, I'll pack it in a bag for you. That'll be 50 dollars.

ssf: iako thoini pito a tilhaz shaonasai lhopilhopishan a taon.
english: I arrived at school at seven today.

ssf: amalhopishiza, itiza sa foifoilh patashan a shinshii monai, lhopilhopishan a shanaotoan mzai, "ilhilhi! pashongkitaz!"
english: It's time for class, the teacher walked into the classroom, and the monitor said: "Stand up! Salute!"

ssf: matonaw malhinona iamin zain, "shinshii maqitan oho."
pinfazaq iamin shinshii tata tosha toro lhopishan a Thao a lalawa ya lhmopish patashan.
english: In class, the teacher taught us the Thau language of numbers.

ssf: montal iamin foifoilh patashan a shinshii malhinona, maqaqoyash iamin tata, tosha, toro lhopishan a qoyash.
english: We followed the teacher to read, we sang the number song.

ssf: mafazaqiza iako manasha wa Thao a lalawa.
english: I have learned many Thau languages.

ssf: tatata wa qali malhopish iako, noma tatata wa qali minfazaq iako sa Thao a lalawa, afoilh iako naak a ina tonmaza.
english: I go to school every day, I learn the Thau language every day, and I want to tell my mother.

ssf: naak a ama wa lhanaz zain Umin.
naak a ina wa lhanaz zain Apin.
itia naak a tantoqash ayozi a minlhafot latata, thitho a lhanaz zain Toba, thitho thoini a kawash makthin tata wa qamishan.
english: I have a brother, his name is Tuba, he is 11 years old.

ssf: lhmopish iamin isa tataal a lhopilhopishan a taon.
english: We study in the same school.

ssf: madadoo iako noma naak a tantoqash ayozi a minlhafot maqaqoyash.
english: Both my brother and I like to sing.

ssf: madadoo iako mraoz, ya pangqaiza wa qali, iamin tata wa taon mosoon amotosi mraoz.
english: I like swimming. During the holidays, our whole family go swimming together.

ssf: mathoaw iako moshnaw faqlho a horoy, shdoo iamin mosoon maqaqoyash noma mraoz.
english: I love meeting new people, we can sing and swim together.

ssf: iamin tata wa taon larima wa thao.
english: There are five people in our family.

ssf: itia iamin tata wa taon latoro a minlhafot.
english: There are three brothers and sisters in our family.

ssf: miasoon iako naak a ama, ina, tantoqash ayozi a minlhafot noma tantoqash binanao'az a minlhafot.
english: I live with my father, mother, brother and sister.

ssf: mathoaw marotaw naak a ama, noma maranash naak a ama.
english: My father is tall and he is a policeman.

ssf: mathoaw mashiqarman naak a ina, noma riqariqaz shiz a shinshii naak a ina.
english: My mother is thin and my mom is a doctor.

ssf: naak a ama itaon mashthaothao mat itan ya malhinona.
english: My father speaks the ethnic language with us at home.

ssf: iamin amakonakataonan ya pinangqaiza mahnariza wa qali.
english: We will all go back to the tribe during the summer vacation.

ssf: amosoon iamin smapok sa bakbaki iako noma naak a tantoqash a minlhafot.
english: My brothers and sisters and I will catch frogs together.

ssf: mathoaw iako moshnaw tata taon a thao.
english: I like our family very much.

ssf: iako thoini masa naak a ina motosi kilhnaqoalh.
english: I went out with my mother today.

ssf: mathoaw dishlom shashano a qali, qali anto mashimzaw anto mani mahnar, fari mathoaw mahaziwhiw.
english: The sky is blue during the day, the weather is neither cold nor hot, and the wind is cool.

ssf: iamin milhongqo iproq kmaan sa paang, patilhazin naam a boot, mathoaw maqalhooz.
english: We ate bread on the grass, the sun was shining on us, and it was very warm.
In the afternoon, the sky turned red.

ssf: makikalhi iako naak a ina, mino sa qali maqolhaqolha.
english: I asked my mother why the sky is red.
Mom said, maybe the typhoon is coming.

ssf: tanlhoaniza wa qali oka s orom, mo'apawiza sa kilhpoz.
english: There were no clouds in the sky at night, and the stars came out.

ssf: amotaoniza isa saran, foilh iako sa kilhpoz mzai.
english: On the way home, I made a wish with the stars

ssf: mihala s qali ingqawan shmiraos, amoqthawan iako mani mosha malhalhiqash.
english: I hope the typhoon doesn't come, I still want to go out to play again.

ssf: naak a lhopilhopishan a taon isai naam a taon a shirshir, tatata wa qali iako mondadaan ya motosi lhopilhopishan a taon, noma mondadaan iako mani makonataon.
english: My school is next to our house, I walk to school every day, and I also walk home.

ssf: ani naam a lhopilhopishan a taon mara'in moqay langqinonay, anto piza s lhmopishoan a azazak, mashtay mafazaq ya timatima.
english: Our school is not big, there are not many students, everyone knows each other.

ssf: mashtay azazak mososoon isa lhopilhopishan a makakakri a danshiqan, mososoon matinhina sa maqarimosoz, noma mosoon malhinona.
english: All the children will gather in the playground, play ball and chat together.

ssf: foifoilh patashan a shinshii mosoon iamin mani malhalhiqash, lhopilhopishan a taon miazai sa mara'in a taon.
english: The teachers also play with us, the school is one big family.

ssf: tatata wa qali iamin thmapo sa bokhaz, mashtay thmapo taon noma piatilaw.
english: We have to clean every day, and everyone has to clean the classroom.

ssf: noma soma wa thao tmitish paziwat noma soma thmapo sa bokhaz.
english: Some people clean the windows, some sweep the floor.

ssf: mashtay iamin thmapo lhopilhopishan a taon a proq, pashtay mindahip thmapo lhopilhopishan a taon, noma tatata wa qali matilatilaw sa lhopilhopishan a taon.
english: We will also clean every corner of the school. Everyone works together, and the school is very clean every day.

ssf: shitosi iako tilha mriqaz naak a apora'in.
english: Yesterday, I went to visit my grandpa in the tribe.

ssf: mathoaw mindaaq iako anto minriqaz naak a apora'in, mathoaw iako mangqtoqto thitho.
english: We haven't seen each other for a long time and I miss him a lot.

ssf: naak a apora'in to mriqaz iakin, pakaan iakin sharitono noma piaqilha iakin poshawil.
english: As soon as grandpa saw me, he invited me to papaya and drink tea.

ssf: naak a apora'in pinalhoiza wa sharitono mathoaw madahon, dado mathoaw taodoo ya kaanin.
english: The papaya grown by grandpa is very sweet and really delicious.

ssf: mathoaw iako miko iqilha naak a apora'in a poshawil, mathoaw maqitan iqilhan.
english: I also like grandpa's tea, it's tasted good too.

ssf: ya saqazi, miasoon iako naak a apoki'ay pinsaqazi iamin pit'ia.
english: At noon, I cooked lunch with my grandma.

ssf: mathoaw naak a apoki'ay pinsaqazi pit'ia manasha pania'an, ianan rosaw, ianan ranaw, ianan bahat, noma ianan mani riaz.
english: Grandma cooked a big lunch, including fish, chicken, pumpkin, and clam.

ssf: kminaaniza konsaqazi, mosoi tamakoan iamin mara shanglaw.
english: After lunch, we went to the vegetable garden to pick vegetables.

ssf: mathoaw naak a apoki'ay lhai iakin bona, lhari noma tilkon, katho motaon.
english: Grandma brought me a lot of sweet potatoes, taro and buckwheat, and asked me to take them home.

ssf: zaik thaithoy amoshaiza iako motaon, ya ishawananiza iako amoqthaiza iako mosoi mriqaz thaithoy.
english: I said goodbye to them and said I'd see them next time.

ssf: thoini foifoilh patashan a shinshii kmatho iamin mosoi ia'ianan nomanoma wa lhkaribosh a lolooman, itosi iamin pitaw mododor mitalha fariw sa qahil.
english: Today the teacher took us to the zoo, and we lined up at the gate to buy tickets.

ssf: motosiza iamin ia'ianan nomanoma wa lhkaribosh a lolooman, foifoilh patashan a shinshii mzai, "romfaz itanamoqtha noma qlhoran itanarikos, shanamanion mriqaz."
english: After entering the zoo, the teacher said, There are birds in the front and snakes in the back

ssf: shongkash iako sa qlhoran, nomawan ani iako amariqaz qlhoran.
english: I'm afraid of snakes, so I don't look at snakes.

ssf: iako mriqaz romfaz mathoaw manasha, thaithoy isoi kawi mathoaw mafarfaz, mriqaz iako mani shmadia malhos isai kawi a mabraq a itmaz.
english: I saw a lot of birds flying around in the trees and saw owls sleeping in tree hollows.

ssf: ia'ianan nomanoma wa lhkaribosh a lolooman ianan sa thomay, tishmamraw noma rokzaw, ani iako kahiwan mriqariqaz izai a lhkaribosh, mathoaw iako thoini maqaran to mriqaz.
english: There are elephants, horses and tigers in the zoo. I have never seen these animals before. I was really happy to see them today.

ssf: pashtiroq iako manasha sa pinashtiroq pariqaz naak a ama ina.
english: I took a lot of pictures and showed them to my parents.

ssf: amonai iako mosoon naak a ama ina ya kahiza.
english: Next time I will come with my parents.

ssf: pangqaiza wa qali thoini, iako masa naak a tantoqash binanao'az a minlhafot shitosi Tai-taang mriqaz naak a pan'amaan.
english: This holiday, my sister and I went to Taitung to visit my uncle.

ssf: iamin i Tai-paak milhongqo sa apoy a barimbin motosi Tai-taang.
english: We took the train from Taipei to Taitung.

ssf: shaonanaiza iamin Tai-taang, naak a pan'amaan patongbarimbin monai barimbin a pangqangqan mashdoo iamin.
english: When we arrived in Taitung, my uncle drove to the station to pick us up.

ssf: barimbin a pangqangqan masa naak a pan'amaan a taon anto ihazish, ya patongbarimbin mohiaw shaonatanto.
english: The station is not far from my uncle's house, and it's just a short drive away.

ssf: naak a pan'amaan a taon a shirshir itia mathoaw mara'ira'in a mara'in a boqan, mosoon ita kmangqtha sa kangqthaan a barimbin motanto mara'in a boqan.
english: There is a big ranch near my uncle's house, and we rode bicycles to the ranch together.

ssf: isai mara'in a boqan, naak a pan'amaan makatho iamin pakaan sisi noma milhongqo sa tishmamraw.
english: In the ranch, my uncle took us to feed the sheep and ride horses.

ssf: mahomhomiza, mosoon iamin motosi mawalhnaq a proq makaan.
english: In the evening, we went to the city to have dinner together.

ssf: mathoaw manasha barimbin mawalhnaq a proq, nomawan matong'o-to-bai iamin motanto.
english: There are a lot of cars in the city, so we go there by motorcycle.

ssf: noma amoshaiza iamin, mriqaz iamin mino o-to-bai qrioin soma, nomawan milhongqo iamin sa baso mosha.
english: When we were about to leave, we found that the motorcycle had been stolen, so we had to leave by bus.

ssf: thoini iamin motaoniza iamin Tai-paak, tihaota iako naak a pan'amaan a o-to-bai qazii ya ongqtoaniza.
english: Now that we are back in Taipei, I don't know if my uncle's motorcycle has been found.

ssf: kahiwan iako inai Baraobaw to langqinonayoan, minalhopishiza iako, mongqthaiza iamin motosi Tai-paak, miaqay iamin ininthawan isa mawalhnaq a proq.
english: When we were young, our family lived in Baraubaw. After I started school, we moved to Taipei and have been living in the city ever since.

ssf: noma minalhopishiza sa mara'in a lhopilhopishan, lhminopish iako minfazaq miniahala inai a thao a kazakazash a minfazaq a patashan, mafazaqiza iako Tai-waan miniahala inai a thao a qbit itia manasha wa nomanoma wa kazakazash.
english: After I went to college, I took a course on aboriginal culture and learned that the aboriginal people in Taiwan have various and rich cultures.

ssf: nomawan, thoini a pinangqaiza mahnariza wa qali, makonakataonan iako noma naak a tantoqash ayozi a minlhafot noma makikalhi iamin tanatoqash, mangqto iamin minfazaq sa naam a Thao a kazakazash.
english: So this summer, my brother and I went back to our tribe to visit the elderly, hoping to understand the culture of our own ethnic group.

ssf: haya toqatoqash makashpashpatiza wa qamishan, noma riqazan sondaiza parhawaywan.
english: The old man is already eighty years old, but he still looks like a middle-aged man.

ssf: makikalhi iako thitho mafazaq thitho nomanoma wa lalawa, mathoaw thitho malhinona Thao a lalawa mathoaw ma'ania, mafazaq mani thitho mashbonon a lalawa, noma Shpoot a lalawa noma Lit-poon a lalawa.
english: I asked him which languages he knew, and he was fluent in Thau, as well as Bunun, Hokkien and Japanese.

ssf: makikalhi iako thitho, noma mafazaq iako, maqa thitho minalhopish Lit-poon a lalawa to azazakoan, to Bonon a thao thitho a binanao'az, noma mathoaw thitho to malhkakrikriw mathoaw kafazaqin thitho manasha Shpoot, nomawan mafazaq thitho manasha anto tataal a lalawa.
english: I asked him to find out that he learned Japanese when he was a child, his wife is an Bunu, and he knows many Hokkien at work, so he can speak so many languages.

ssf: mosoon iamin malhalhinona, noma izai tanatoqash foilh manasha moribosh a kazakazash.
english: During our interview, the old man talked about a lot of traditional knowledge about hunting.

ssf: sharaqian anto shiroan iamin mafazaq sa molhthkiz a lalawa, kanoniza polaonin sa bahi iamin pasain sa ling-waa, shdoo iamin moqtha tmaza.
english: Although we could't fully understand it, we could record it on our cell phones and listen to it more.

ssf: maora iako mita wa Thao a kazakazash to azazakoan, mayaw iako mzai Thao mita.
english: When I was young, I didn't understand the culture of my ethnic group, and I was a little embarrassed that I was an aborigine.

ssf: mafazaqiza iako thoini Thao a nomanoma wa kazakazash, mangqto iako mathoaw maqaran noma maqitan to Thao iako.
english: The more I know, the more I feel that being a Thau is unique and something to be proud of.

ssf: thoini a saqaziza, amotaoniza shashoaz ayozi a minlhafot.
english: My younger brother is going home this evening.

ssf: motosi iako noma naak a apoki'ay farifariwan sa pania'an fariw sa ranaw, kontanlhoan apintata iamin maqitan a akaanin pakaan naak a shashoaz ayozi a minlhafot.
english: My grandma and I went to the market to buy chickens and prepared a delicious dinner for my younger brother.

ssf: mon'ioto iamin farifariwan shanglaw a taon, farifariwan shanglaw a taon itia manasha wa maqitaqitan a shanglaw.
english: We passed the vegetable stand, which had a lot of fresh green vegetables.

ssf: finariw iamin sangriz, sipo noma maqolha wa sai-poo.
english: We bought water spinach, yams and carrots.

ssf: isa shirshir farifariwan ribosh a bonlhaz a taon a talima mzai, "mathoaw madahon naak a ong-lai noma qalop. fariwoan!"
english: The owner of the nearby fruit stand said: "My pineapples and peaches are very sweet. Buy some!"

ssf: mon'ioto iamin farifariwan bonlhaz a taon talima mzai, "noma sa afariwin oho qa? mathoaw mara'in noma maramo thoini a ranaw, latata wa ranaw toro a shaba."
english: We passed the meat stall, and the boss said, "What do you want to buy? Today's chickens are big and fat, and one is 300 NTD."

ssf: naak a apoki'ay mzai mathoaw manasha toali, zaiwan thitho talima potladado sa toali.
english: Grandma thought it was too expensive and asked the boss if it could be cheaper.

ssf: kanoniza mzai s talima mathoaw ladado a toali, anto potladado sa toali.
english: But the boss said that it is already very cheap and cannot be reduced any further.

ssf: shirshir a talima mzai, "onaiwan fariw naak a rosaw, mathoaw mara'in noma ladado a toali naak a rosaw."
english: The boss next door said, come and buy my fish, my fish is big and cheap.

ssf: mingqarayza finariw iamin ranaw noma finariw iamin mani rosaw, noma motaon pintata noma tata wa pangka manasha pania'an.
english: In the end we bought chicken and fish, and went home to cook a table of food.
After waiting for a long time, it was already dark.

ssf: shashoaz ayozi a minlhafot malhinona sa ling-wa mzai, kanshitashan anto dai pangqa, amoqtha wa pangqaiza wa qali amotaoniza.
english: The younger brother called back and said that the army suddenly couldn't take a vacation and would not be back until the next Sunday.

ssf: noma apoki'ay mzai, "pania'an mathoaw manasha, palalawa pashtay monai mosoon kmaan!"
english: Grandma said that she has cooked so much, so let's eat together!

ssf: malalawa iamin piathaothaon noma horoy, monai mosoon kontanlhoan kmaan.
english: We invited friends and family to have a great dinner together.

ssf: itia naak a tata wa tataal lhmopish a horoy zain Rongqoan, miaqay min'a'aora kmatho thitho a aniamin.
english: I have a classmate named Rungquan, he often forgets to bring things.

ssf: ya malhopish miaqay thitho mashimol tataal lhmopish a horoy patatash, tatitish noma patashan.
english: During class, he borrowed pencils, erasers or notebooks from his classmates.

ssf: motal, moposhaz, motoroz, mashtay pashimol thitho aniamin.
english: Once, twice, three times, everyone would lend him something.

ssf: noma maqa maqarman thitho minzawash miaqay mashimol anto poshoqish thitho.
english: But he has a bad habit of often borrowing things but not returning them.

ssf: mingqarayza mashtay anto pashimol thitho aniamin.
english: In the end, no one wanted to borrow anything from him.

ssf: tata wa qali, mashtay iamin mosoon motosi kilhnaqoalh.
english: One day, we all went on an outing together.

ssf: makontosi iamin isa saran, apishtopoan sa Rongqoan, noma min'aora thitho kmatho sa qahil.
english: On the way, Rungquan wanted to go to the bathroom, but he forgot to bring toilet paper.

ssf: amashimol thitho horoy qahil, zain thitho a horoy mzai, "ani iako mani kminatho"
english: He borrowed toilet paper from his classmates, but everyone told him that I didn't bring them either.

ssf: noma izai Rongqoan minsasalpo noma thmanit. minboqnor thitho mzai, "minoiza pashtay manion anto pashimol iakin qahil!"
english: Rungquan burst into tears. He said angrily, why don't everyone lend me toilet paper!

ssf: tataal lhmopish a horoy foilh thitho, maqa miaqay iho anto min'ananak makatho sa qahil, noma iho ya shimimol nomanoma anto poshoqish!
english: The classmate told him, because you didn't bring it yourself, and you wouldn't return the things lent to you!

ssf: simaqiza malhopish iamin, Rongqoan mathoaw matinhomhom motosi lhopilhopishan a taon, thitho shmimol a nomanoma polhthkizin poshoqish lhai sa tataal lhmopish a horoy.
english: The next day at school, Rungquan arrived at school early and returned everything he had borrowed from his classmates.

ssf: Rongqoan mathoaw amazayza thitho a tataal lhmopish a horoy, noma foilh thaithoy dai ya kahiza thitho amin'ananak kmatho nomanoma aniamin, noma anoniza thaithoy sa tataal lhmopish a horoy pashimol thitho aniamin.
english: Rungquan apologized to the students and said that he would definitely bring his own things in the future, and thanked the classmates for their willingness to lend him things before.

ssf: kataonan a moribosh a thao naak a ama.
english: My dad is a hunter of the tribe.

ssf: to azazakoan iako, naak a ama noma pan'amaan motosi hodon ya tanlhoan, kmatho thaithoy sa fonosh noma pothoom.
english: When I was little, my dad and uncle would go out at night with hunting knives and guns.

ssf: ya shashanoiza, kmatho thaithoy mara sa matiqto a lhkaribosh makonataon.
english: At daybreak, they returned with their prey.

ssf: ya to soma wazish, ya to soma rawaz, itia mani sa alhoa masa lhizashan.
english: Sometimes it was a boar, sometimes a flying squirrel, and occasionally a pheasant.

ssf: mapa'inqbit thaithoy lhkaribosh a bonlhaz isai kataonan a pitaw, patara thaithoy soma wa thao.
english: They would divide the prey at the entrance of the village and share it with the tribe.

ssf: miaqay iako miko ontal naak a ama moribosh.
english: Every time I quarreled with my father, I wanted to go hunting with my father.

ssf: naak a ama mzai ya mara'iniza amakatho iakin montal moribosh.
english: Dad said that he would take me with me when I grew up.

ssf: kataonan a ayozi mafazaq mani kmalawa sa toqris, potoqris noma kmalawa qadop thaithoy ya moribosh.
english: The men of the tribe also trap their prey, making lasso traps and rock traps.

ssf: mathoaw naak a ama ma'ania tmoqris, ama mzai, "haya wa toqris apoqto sa alhoa, amariqaz iamin lhkaribosh a sapaz, noma atmoqris iamin pisoi sinaranan lhkaribosh."
english: My dad is very good at making lasso traps. Dad said that this is used to catch pheasants. We have to carefully observe the footprints of the prey, and the traps should be placed on the path of the prey.

ssf: mangqto iako mohiaw montal parhaway noma tanatoqash motosi hodon moribosh, nomawan tatata wa qali minfazaq iako kmalawa sa toqris, amohiaw naak a toqris shdoo mara sa lhkaribosh.
english: In order to go hunting with adults as soon as possible, I practiced making traps every day, and soon my traps can really catch prey.

ssf: minriqaz naak a ama iakin mzai, "aminma'ania wa moribosh a thao iho ya kahiza."
english: Dad saw it and told me that I will be a very good hunter in the future.

ssf: mara'iniza iako thoini, mapa iako naak a fotolh noma lhpazishan montal naak a ama iakin mosoi moribosh.
english: Now that I have grown up, I carry my bow and arrows and go hunting with my father.

ssf: motaon iamin kataonan ya itia matiqto sa lhkaribosh patara pakaan soma wa thao.
english: When returning to the village, share the hunted prey with the tribe.

ssf: ama mzai apaplish iamin, piakalingkin manion molhthkiz tanatoqash, mathoaw maqitan pimbahi iamin moribosh mara manasha wa lhkaribosh.
english: Dad said, we want to thank the ancestors for their blessings, so that we have a lot of prey to harvest.
I was late for school this morning.

ssf: motosi iako lhopilhopishan a taon, min'aora iako kminatho sa antotoan patashan.
english: When I was going to school, I forgot to bring my backpack.

ssf: nomanoma wa aniamin anto kminatho iako.
english: I didn't bring anything with me.

ssf: ya lhmopish, iako miasoon naak a tataal lhmopish a horoy mriqaz sa patashan.
english: During class, I and my classmates read the textbook together.

ssf: ya motazam, tataal lhmopish a horoy shimolik sa patatash noma tatitish.
english: During the exam, a classmate lent me a pen and an eraser.

ssf: foifoilh patashan a shinshii mzai, "milhhomhom ya moqthawan, niza to saqazian!"
english: The teacher told me, \Wake up earlier next time and don't be late again!\""

ssf: naak a maqitan a horoy mzai Hoqo, Thao a azazak thitho mani.
english: My good friend's name is Huqu, and he is also an Thau child.

ssf: miasoon iamin isa Baraobaw a kataonan lhmopish.
english: We study together in the Baraubaw tribe.

ssf: miarain miasoon iamin tonmaza apo malhinona kahiwan a lalawa, mathoaw ma'ania iamin ya malhinona Thao a lalawa.
english: We often listen to the elders telling stories together, and we both can speak the Thau proficiently.

ssf: mathoaw marotaw iako mani maramo, mathoaw Hoqo matompiq mani mashiqarman.
english: I am tall and overweight, while Huqu is short and thin.

ssf: Hoqo mathoaw ma'aloz'oz, pashtay madadoo thitho.
english: Huqu is very energetic, and everyone likes him a lot.

ssf: lhopilhopishan a taon pinkazakaza sa boot a makakakri thoini, lhopilhopishan a taon kmalawa piza wa qbit malantatnor.
english: Today was the school's sports day, and the school organized many competitions.

ssf: ianan sa shmoroz klhiw, psaq qarimosoz, malalia, minparaw, kmolhpazishan.
english: There were tug of war, soccer, running, dancing, and archery.
I participated in the running competition.

ssf: malalia iako taobokbok, mathoaw qarof paktalhom.
english: When I was running, I fell down, and my knees were bleeding.

ssf: kanoniza milhilhi iako, moqthawan makonamoqtha malalia.
english: But I stood up and continued running forward.

ssf: shaonapispis iako, pashtay a thao mathoaw ma'alah'a.
english: Everyone was happy when I reached the finish line.

ssf: sharaqian anto mara sa makintata, kanoniza mathoaw ma'alah'a iako, maqa mokaktoniza iako malantatnor.
english: Although I didn't get first place, I'm glad because I completed the race.

ssf: minontal iako naak a ama tilha mriqaz naak a pan'amaan.
english: Yesterday, my father and I visited my uncle.

ssf: mzai thitho iamin, taon a tafoq ianan latata wa tabraqan.
english: He told us that there was a hole in the roof of his house.

ssf: kashiqitan thitho sa tafoq, initafoq panthathak panaproq.
english: He fell off the roof while repairing it.

ssf: ama kminatho sa qnoan a bonlhaz masa shawiki lhai pan'amaan.
english: My father brought beef and betel nuts for my uncle.

ssf: iako masa pan'amaan isa laqop malhalhinona, mathoaw mzai thitho manasha sa kahiwan a lalawa patmazan iakin.
english: My uncle and I chatted in the room, and he shared many stories.

ssf: amoshaiza iako, noma pan'amaan lhomfaan iakin mzai minrotawiza noma mindirodiroiza.
english: Before I left, my uncle praised me for growing taller and becoming more handsome.

ssf: zaik "pan'amaan a koskos ya minqitaniza, moqthawan monai naak a taon kilhnaqoalh."
english: I said, When your foot gets better

ssf: isa 2022 wa kawash, zing-hoo pishfazaq miniahala inai a thao sa thao a tnoran shdooiza moqayza matash sa thao a qbit a lhanaz.
english: In 2022, the government announced that indigenous identification cards can include tribal names separately.

ssf: iako makikalhi sa mathoaw monsai zing-hoo thmadoq mindaaq sa thao a tnoran moqayza matash sa thao a qbit a lhanaz kataonan a parhaway Pano.
english: I interviewed Panu, a young tribal member who has long been advocating for the inclusion of tribal names on identification cards.

ssf: amatilhdoo iako thitho inai pangqaiza wa qali motosi thitho a taon makikalhi thitho.
english: We had arranged to visit his home this holiday for the interview.

ssf: makikalhi thitho to isisoa, thitho pishfazaq iakin miakoza thitho a lhanaz minakanai, noma kmatho iakin mani mafazaq sa thitho a taon a thao, noma thitho a kataonan.
english: During the interview, he introduced to me the origin of his name and also introduced me to his family and tribe.

ssf: makikalhi iako thitho mino amingqtha sa lhanaz, sasaz a pinatash anto taodoo qa?
english: I asked him why he insisted on changing his name. Wasn't the old registration method sufficient?

ssf: thitho montazaikin mzai, maqa pasain Shpoot a matash anto pobalabalay pishfazaq thitho a lhanaz, soma wa thao amalalawa thitho mzai "Pa shinshii." nomawan kafazaan soma.
english: He told me that using Chinese characters could not accurately convey his name, and others would still call him \Ba Xian Sheng

ssf: Pano mzai, "miniahala inai a thao matash a lhanaz shonda sa naam a lhanaz, naak a lhanaz mia'azo naam a thao a qbit, naam a taon a qbit, naam a tnoran, mangqto ianan manasha sa thao a qbit aposhoqish ananak a lhanaz."
english: Panu said, \The names written in indigenous languages are our true names. My name represents our ethnic group

ssf: tilha montal iako naak a apoki'ay mosoi farifariwan pashatalha sa aniamin, kathon apoki'ay manasha mat'anak malhoyza wa shanglaw mo'ioto, noma kmalawa miniahala inai a thao maqitan a akaanin lhai pashta.
english: Yesterday, I went to the market with my grandmother to set up a stall. My grandmother brought a lot of vegetables that she grew herself and also prepared indigenous cuisine for everyone.

ssf: pashtay miko apoki'ay a pashatalha'an, makamon noma lhari manasha sa thao finariw, manasha sa thao monai kmaan pintatan thitho a pania'an.
english: Everyone loved my grandmother's stall. Many people bought the chilis and taro, and many people came to taste the dishes she cooked.

ssf: thitho sa pintatan a tazakas noma sonda wa afo mathoaw maqitan ya kaanin, noma ianan pasain rafon masa romrom poqana'an, shmorawath shazik manasha sa kilhnaqoalh a thao, pashta molhthkiz monai naam a pashatalha'an mododor.
english: The ferns and sticky rice she cooked were delicious, as well as the braised pork with maqaw pepper and wild boar meat. The flavors attracted many customers, and everyone lined up at our stall.

ssf: apoki'ay ya pintata sa aniamin, ishirshir iako malalawa kilhnaqolh a thao. ishirshir minbabaw iako mzai az'az mat'anak iamin malhoiza wa shanglaw, min'ananak maqitan, ohiawan monai fariw!
english: While my grandmother was cooking, I was on the side attracting customers. I shouted, \The vegetables are self-grown

ssf: naam a aniamin mohiaw fariwiniza, apoki'ay mzai, "maqa ianan iho to mindahip."
english: Our goods sold out quickly, and my grandmother said, \It's all thanks to your help.\""

ssf: izai a makakakri, mafazaq iako sa izai miniahala inai a thao a pinalhoiza noma kakaanin a infazaqin, noma ananak shmozap pashatalha sa aniamin a shkoda.
english: Through this event, I learned about indigenous plants and food and experienced the hard work of running a stall.

ssf: mriqaz naak a apoki'ay mathoaw miko sa kahiwan a kakaanin, mathoaw iako pazazai noma matingqaran.
english: Seeing my grandmother's passion for traditional food, I feel very proud and honored.
